THE W. F. DALZELL. THE HIGHLANDER. (Circuit Court of Appeals Second Circuit. October 24, 1922.) No. 49. Foley & Martin, of New York City, for libelants. Bigham, Englar & Jones, of New York City (Leonard J. Matteson and Amdrew J. McElhinney, both of New York City, of counsel), for claimant of the W. F. Balzell. Mackim, Brown & Van Wyek, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for claimant the Highlander.

Before ROGERS, MANTON, and MAYER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
